# ============================================================
# Monorepo root: only `app/` is part of THIS git repository.
# Every other top-level sub-project directory has its own git repo.
# Only the project named `app` is tracked; all other root-level
# directories are ignored recursively.
# ============================================================

# Allow app/ (negation of /app/ would also need negation of app/*/*).
# Since we only want app/ tracked, the simplest correct rule is:
#  - ignore every root dir by name
#  - but only when not `app`

# Use a path-specific ruleset via `app/` being the only tracked subtree:
app/
app/**
!/app/**
!/app/

# Everything else at the root is NOT part of this repo.
# (We rely on git's default: untracked content is harmless; we just
# won't stage it. Listing specific sub-repo names below as a safety
# net in case anyone runs `git add .` by mistake.)
# ============================================================
# Sibling project dirs (do NOT remove these without re-checking)
